question: Madison and Ethan have 137 minutes to walk to the school together. It takes them 29 minutes to get to the corner where the park is. It takes them another 11 minutes to get to the bank. How much longer do they have to get to school without being late?
answer:
Madison and Ethan arrive at the park with 137 - 29 = <<137-29=108>>108 minutes left to reach the bank.
They then arrive at the bank and have 108 - 11 = <<108-11=97>>97 minutes left to get to school without being late.
#### 97
